Package: deflist
Type: Package
Title: A read only list-like object that accesses it's elements via a function
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Bradley Buchsbaum
Authors@R: person("Bradley", "Buchsbaum", email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The "deflist" class can be used to model "deferred access" to data or computations by routing indexed list access to a function. 
    This effect may be useful when one requires sequential list-like access to data but cannot afford to hold all the data in memory at once.
License: LGPL (>= 2.1)
